          'I have contributed to and maintained Lightbeam, a browser extension that visualizes first and third-party trackers.',
      },
      {
        title: 'Firefox Developer Tools Debugger',
        description:
          'I served as a community maintainer for the Firefox Developer Tools Debugger project.',
      },
      {
        title: 'Software Developer coach at Raise.dev and MLH Fellowship',
        description:
          'I guided undergraduates in contributing to open-source projects, provided career advice, and prepared them for internships or full-time jobs in Software Engineering. Through this program, I mentored open-source contributors to popular repositories such as React Native Core, AWS Amplify, and Slate.js.',
      },
    ]}
    youtube="sINIM0QX2Y8"
  >
    <Fragment slot="content">
      <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight dark:text-white sm:text-3xl mb-2">My Open Source journey</h3>
      I got into open source through the Outreachy program. Read my blog posts on the Open Source topic.
